title: vektor_cr-21
body:
Vektor CR-21, or "Compact Rifle, 21st Century" is a prototype [[assault_rifle|assault rifle]] made by Denel Land Systems of South Africa. It is essentially a Vektor R-4 mechanism in a bullpup configuration encased in a polymer casing. Because of that, the weapon actually traces its heritage to [[IMI_Galil|Galil]], which in turn has its roots in the venerable [[AK_47|AK-47]].

Due to its polymer casing and simplified form of Kalashnikov's long-stroke piston mechanism, the gun is very light. Also, its overall smooth, curved shape gives it a very sci-fi appearance. However, because it failed to achieve sales in both domestic and international markets, it is very rare.

title: mighty_gunvolt
body:
[b][i]Mighty Gunvolt[/i][/b] ([i]Gal☆Gunvolt[/i] in Japan) is a retro-styled action-platforming game by "Inti Creates":http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Inti_Creates as a spin-off to their [i][[Azure Striker Gunvolt]][/i] series. It features a crossover of [i][[Azure Striker Gunvolt]][/i], [i][[Mighty No. 9]][/i], and [i][[gal_gun|Gal☆Gun]][/i] in a Famicom/NES-styled mini-game reminiscent of "[i]Mighty Final Fight[/i]":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mighty_Final_Fight with each series' representative protagonists as they attempt to foil the Sumeragi Group's plot of hunting down idols to serve as a replacement for Lumen. The gameplay is a [i]heavily[/i] stripped-down version of [i][[Mega Man (series)|]][/i], as players go through a small set of linear stages with only each character's standard weapon to take on legions of enemies from their respective series. 

A sequel, [i][[Mighty Gunvolt Burst]][/i], was released in 2017 for the Nintendo Switch and 3DS with subsequent re-releases on PlayStation 4 and Windows PC.

title: mighty_gunvolt_burst
body:
[b][i]Mighty Gunvolt Burst[/i][/b] ([i]Gal☆Gunvolt Burst[/i] in Japan and the PlayStation 4 version) is the sequel to the 2014 action-platforming game, [i][[Mighty Gunvolt]][/i]. Unlike the previous game, this installment features a proper crossover of [i][[Mighty No. 9]][/i], [i][[Azure Striker Gunvolt]][/i], [i][[gal_gun|Gal☆Gun]][/i] into a full-fledged game. In an attempt to bring the ill-received [i]Mighty No. 9[/i] into a positive light, this game's plot follows after the events of that game, where [[beck_(mighty_no._9)|Beck]] finds himself unable to leave the virtual-reality training program that Professor White had created for him to train Beck for future battles, which is where he runs into a teenage boy who resembles Gunvolt and claims to be the program's GM, challenging Beck to face off against his Septimal powers. Similarly, in [[Gunvolt]]'s scenario, while on a mission one night, he and [[joule_(gunvolt)|Joule]] gets sucked into the virtual-reality training by a blinding light that Beck was trapped in, except they were being challenged by Beck into a tournament to take him and Mighty Number siblings into battle.

Expanding on its predecessor, [i]Mighty Gunvolt Burst[/i] features a full-length [i][[Mega Man (series)|]][/i]-esque campaign built around the "Burst" mechanic, where players can earn score bonuses for finishing off enemies in close-range, and features a robust weapon customization system where, depending on the character, can create various types of attacks for their character of choice with each character possessing unique abilities of their own. Initially, [i]Gal☆Gun[/i] was shown less prominently than the previous game, but eventually became featured along with the other two series through later updates and releases. Some of the other characters from each represented series, such as [[call_(mighty_no._9)|Call]] ([i]Mighty No. 9[/i]), [[acura_(gunvolt)|Copen]] ([i]Azure Striker Gunvolt[/i]), and [[kurona_(galgun)|Kurona]] ([i]Gal☆Gun[/i]) later made playable appearances as DLC characters for the game.

title: mighty_no._9
body:
[b][i]Mighty No. 9[/i][/b] is a side-scrolling action game, co-developed by "Keiji Inafune":http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Keiji_Inafune, Comcept LLC, and "Inti Creates":http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Inti_Creates together with an all-star team of experienced [[Mega Man (series)|]] developers. It shares the spirit and DNA of the classic Mega Man series, while also introducing new innovative gameplay elements.

The game follows the titular Mighty No. 9, [[beck_(mighty_no._9)|Beck]], along with his companion [[call_(mighty_no._9)|Call]] as they their battle against the Mighty Numbers after a viral outbreak causes nearly every robot in America to go berserk and turn against mankind.

The project and its multiple stretch goals were successfully funded on Kickstarter from September 1st until October 2nd 2013 with more than $4,000,000 pledged. Its release date was originally planned for April 2015, but was delayed multiple times until it was finally released on June 21, 2016 for home systems. Meanwhile, it has yet to be released for any portable system.

Due to a host of problems behind the scenes and the finished product coming out somewhat underwhelming, it is regarded as one of the worst games of 2016 and has been set as an example of crowdfunded projects gone wrong. With the negative reception towards the game and Inafune, [i]Mighty No. 9[/i] unfortunately ended up becoming his swan song and his company was bought out by [[level-5|Level-5]]. Despite this, Beck (and later the other Mighty Numbers) would go on to feature prominently in the [i]Mighty Gunvolt[/i] series of spin-offs, which have been met with much more positive reception.

title: ray_(mighty_no._9)
body:
A downloadable character of [i][[Mighty No. 9]][/i], and a spiritual analogue to [[proto man|Proto Man]] [spoiler](backstory and origins)[/spoiler] and [[zero (mega man)|Zero]] (gameplay and character concepts). She was originally planed for a boss battle, however, thanks to the partnership with Deep Silver, she also became a playable character with her own story.

RAY is a mysterious robot who somehow posses similar Xel-manipuating abilities to [[beck (mighty no. 9)|Beck]] as she can also assimilate Xels from other robots, however, her physical body is constantly deteriorating from Xel depravation and her sanity gradually slipping. Unlike Beck, she is a melee-oriented character à la Zero, as she fights enemies using her claws that can perform a 3-attack combo with a powerful finishing attack and a spinning tackle that allows her to charge into enemies. She can also gain "Variation Codes" from the Mighty Numbers where her arm mutates into a different weapon.

[spoiler]Throughout her DLC campaign, it is revealed that her real name was Raychel, and likely to be "Mighty No. 0" as she was created by [[William White|Professor William White]] at an attempt of making a freely-evolving robot that can assimilate and manipulate Xels. Her body deteriorating is due to the faulty programming of her Xel Core.[/spoiler]

She also makes another appearance in [i][[Mighty Gunvolt Burst]][/i] as a DLC character as well along with [[acura (gunvolt)|Copen]] from [i]Azure Striker Gunvolt[/i] and [[kurona (galgun)|Kurona]] from [i]Gal☆Gun[/i].

body: A series of helper transport robots of [i][[Mighty No. 9]][/i], analogous to [[eddie (mega man)|Eddie]]. They provide items and power-ups to players in [i]Mighty No. 9[/i] at predetermined points in a stage, with the quantity and quality of the items improving based on how frequently the player loses lives. title: call_d
body:
One of the nine character designs pitched for [[call_(mighty_no._9)|Call]] in [i][[Mighty No. 9]][/i], pitched by [[inafune_keiji|Keiji Inafune]]. She is depicted wearing a red dress with dark purple arm joins and dark yellow shoulder joints, with a striped violet and purple skirt, red [[ankle boots]], and fuchsia/black gloves. She also has [[blue eyes]] [[long hair|long]] [[purple hair]] with [[blunt bangs]], worn in [[twin tails]] that resembles [[dr. wily (mega man)|Dr. Wily's]] iconic hairstyle.

[spoiler]Although this design did not make it as the final design for Call, as the [[Call F]] design by [[natsume_yuuji|Yuuji Natsume]] won the majority of votes from the online poll for Call's character design, Call D did however became the design used for [[trinity_(mighty_no._9)|Trinity]] restored after Beck cured her corrupt programming that caused her mutation and go berserk that started the viral outbreak in America.[/spoiler]

title: indian_clothing
body:
Clothing evolved simple garments like kaupina, langota, salwaar kameez, lungi, [[sari]], gamcha, and loincloths to cover the body into elaborate costumes not only used in daily wear, but also on festive occasions, as well as rituals and dance performances.

India has a great diversity in terms of weaves, fibers, colours, and material of clothing. Sometimes, color codes are followed in clothing based on the religion and ritual concerned. The clothing in India also encompasses the wide variety of Indian embroidery, prints, handwork, embellishment, styles of wearing clothes. 

This can include a mix of Indian traditional clothing and western styles can be seen in India.

title: shu_(hokuto_no_ken)
body:
[b]Shu[/b] ([b]シュウ[/b]) is the character from [[Hokuto no Ken]].

He is the successor of the Nanto Hakurou Ken (南斗白鷺拳, "South Star White Heron Fist") style, which specializes in kicks. He represents the Star of Benevolence (仁星, Jinsei), as well as a friend of [[rei (hokuto no ken)|Rei]]. Shu was once [[souther|Souther's]] second-in-command until he met a young [[Kenshiro]], who was participating in a kumite against ten Nanto Seiken practitioners. Shu and challenged Ken as his final opponent and defeated Ken, but forfeited his eyesight (by slicing his own eyes) after his victory so that Kenshiro's life would be spared. After the Nuclear War, Shuu leads a resistance movement against Souther and his empire and is reunited with the now grown Kenshiro.

body: A God Man Digimon. title: borgward_iv
body:
The Borgward IV, officially designated Schwerer Ladungsträger Borgward B IV (heavy explosive carrier Borgward B IV), was a German remote-controlled demolition vehicle used in World War II.

Borgward originally developed the B IV as an ammunition carrier, but it was found unsuitable. It was also tested as a remote minesweeper, but was too vulnerable to mines and too expensive. During the Battle of France, German engineers from the 1st Panzer Division converted 10 Panzer I Ausf Bs into demolition and mine clearing vehicles, using them to place timed charges on bunkers or minefields without losing the vehicle. The Waffenamt found the idea valuable, and ordered the B IV's development as a remote-controlled demolition vehicle. The first vehicles were delivered in 1942.[1]

The Borgward IV was much heavier than the Goliath, and carried a much larger payload. The Borgward IV was operated by radio and the Goliath was wire guided, due to the Borgward IV's much longer range a driver in the vehicle would bring it independently to its destination before dismounting and conducting it to its target by radio. When it reached the target, the vehicle would drop the charge and leave the danger area. This put Borgward IV operators in great danger. While the Borgward IV was armored, its armor was inadequate by 1942-43, and its larger size than the Goliath made it much easier to spot.

[b]Gossip[/b] is an act of spreading mass medium of rumor, especially about a character's personal or private affairs of other character, either to reinforce morality and accountability or to passively aggress the targeted character, [[embarrassed|embarrassing]] them in the process. Also known as [b]dishing[/b] or [b]tattling[/b].

In [[Tokimeki Memorial]], less frequently [[dating|dated]] girls will become [[angry]] and attempt to gossip to others (indicated by a [[bomb]]), severely reducing the player's reputation in the school.

h4. See also

* [[bullying]]
* [[embarrassed]], the result of being gossiped.

title: mile_(noukin)
body:
Mile is the main protagonist of the light novel series [[watashi nouryoku wa heikinchi de tte itta yo ne!|Watashi, nouryoku wa heikinchi de tte itta yo ne!]] (English Title: Didn't I Say to Make My Abilities Average in the Next Life?!).  She is a hunter (adventurer) living in a pseudo-fantasy world.  In her previous life she died saving the life of someone important for the future of humanity, and as a reward a god granted her reincarnation into another world with enhanced abilities.  Her response on enhancing her abilities was "Please, make my abilities average!", as she already lived a life standing out and wished for a quieter life.  Her abilities though end up far from what she had in mind for average, with many aspects of her life determined by mid-range (average between the lowest and highest values), thus her new life is anything but average.

Mile is the alias of Adele von Ascham as she lives her life as an adventurer.  In her previous life her name was Kurihara Misato (栗原海里).  The characters for Misato (海里) can also be read as Kairi (nautical mile), and is the origin of both her alias and her previous name.

Mile is a member of an all-girls hunter party that goes by the name The Crimson Vow (赤き誓い Akaki Chikai). Its members consists of [[mavis_von_austien|Mavis]], [[pauline_(noukin)|Pauline]], [[reina_(noukin)|Reina]], and Mile herself.

title: ilpalazzo
body:
A main character of the series [[Excel Saga]].  He has yellow eyes with slit-like pupils, and long silver hair.

Ilpalazzo is the mysterious leader of the organization ACROSS and plans on conquering the world through it.  He directly issues missions to his agents [[Excel]], [[Hyatt]], and [[Elgala]], but usually leaves out the details of these missions.  While Excel, Hyatt, and Elgala are the only real agents shown under his command, the full size and extent of his organization is unknown.  At minimum his organization holds a vast amount of financial and technological power.

Ilpalazzo's archenemy is Dr. Kabapu, the head of the City Environmental Security Administration.  Dr. Kabapu tries to do everything in his power to prevent Ilpalazzo from achieving world conquest.

title: sonic_the_hedgehog_(2006)
body:
[b]Sonic the Hedgehog[/b] (ソニック・ザ・ヘッジホッグ [i]Sonikku za Hejjihoggu[/i]) is a 2006 platform game made to celebrate the 15th anniversary of the [[Sonic (series)|]] franchise. It was developed by [[Sonic Team]] and published by [[Sega]] for Xbox 360 and PlayStation 3. It introduced the recurring character [[Silver the Hedgehog]]. Due to its lack of distinct title, the game is commonly referred to as [b]Sonic '06[/b] or [b]Sonic 2006[/b]. The game faced development issues which resulted the product being rushed. Upon release, it was widely criticized for its numerous gameplay glitches and long loading times.

In this game, [[Sonic the Hedgehog|Sonic]] and [[Tails (Sonic)|]] investigate [[Dr. Eggman]]'s Incredible Interstellar Amusement Park, where Dr. Eggman admits to the public that he has turned over a new leaf and has created an amusement park to make up for his past deeds. title: sonic_mania
body:
[b]Sonic Mania[/b] (ソニックマニア [i]Sonikku Mania[/i]) is a side-scrolling platformer video game developed by Christian Whitehead, Headcannon and PagodaWest Games. It was published by [[Sega]] and released in 2017 for the Nintendo Switch, Xbox One, PlayStation 4 and PC. The game acts as a celebration of the Sonic series' 25th anniversary, and follows [[Sonic the Hedgehog|Sonic]], [[Tails (Sonic)|Tails]], [[Knuckles the Echidna|Knuckles]] as they try to keep [[Dr. Eggman]] and the Hard Boiled Heavies from harnessing a mysterious new energy source, the Phantom Ruby. The story of the game also ties with [[Sonic Forces]], released on the same year.

A definitive version of the game titled [b]Sonic Mania Plus[/b] was released on 17 July 2018, which features the return of [[Mighty the Armadillo]] and [[Ray the Flying Squirrel]] as playable characters, as well as a 4-player Competition Mode and Encore Mode.

title: sonic_forces
body:
[b]Sonic Forces[/b] (ソニックフォース Sonikku Fōsu) is a platform video game developed by [[Sonic Team]] and published by [[Sega]]. It was released on 7 November 2017 for PC, Nintendo Switch, PlayStation 4 and Xbox One. Sonic Forces follows [[Sonic the hedgehog|Sonic]] as he joins a resistance force to take back the planet after [[Dr. Eggman]]'s Eggman Empire took over 99% of it with the help of Eggman's henchmen, the Phantom Ruby, and a mysterious new villain known as [[Infinite (Sonic)|Infinite]]. The story of the game also ties with [[Sonic Mania]], released in the same year.

The game marks the return of the collaboration between both Classic Sonic and Modern Sonic since [[Sonic Generations]], and in addition, Sonic Forces also introduces a third gameplay mode featuring the "Avatar", the player's own custom-created character. The game serves, along with Sonic Mania, as a celebration of Sonic series' 25th anniversary.

body:
A 2020 anime by [[trigger_(company)|Studio Trigger]].

Throughout history, humans have been at odds with Beastmen—a species capable of changing shape due to their genetic "Beast Factor." Because of this conflict, Beastmen have been forced into hiding. Anima City serves as a safe haven for these oppressed individuals to live free from human interference.

During a festival celebrating the town's 10th anniversary, [[Kagemori Michiru]], a human who suddenly turned into a [[tanuki]], finds that Anima City is a far cry from paradise. After witnessing an explosion in the square, she is confronted by [[Ogami Shirou]], a seemingly indestructible [[wolf]] and sworn protector of all Beastmen. As they pursue the criminals behind the bombing, the two discover that Michiru is anything but an ordinary Beastman, and look to investigate her mysterious past and uncanny abilities. Could she turn out to be the missing link between Humans and Beastmen?

Cervantes' father, Philip de Leon, was a privateer sent on a special mission from the Spanish king to loot in the name of Spain. One day, he sailed closely to an English ship with intent to loot it, only to find out too late that it was a warship. He was taken by surprise, his ship was destroyed, and he died along with it. Cervantes was devastated. Cervantes grew up full of pride over his father who was a great sailor, but became a notorious pirate because of his father's death.

Cervantes himself became the scourge of the seas, wielding Soul Edge and reaping souls, before he was defeated and lost part of his weapon at the hands of [[Taki (Soulcalibur)|Taki]] and [[Sophitia Alexandra]]. Since then, he journeys to recover the weapon that was taken from him.

Cervantes is the biological father of [[Isabella Valentine|Isabella "Ivy" Valentine]].

h6. Visual Characteristics
Cervantes has peach skin [[long_hair|long]] [[white hair]] with a violet tint and [[blue eyes]] and sported a full [[mustache]]. When under the influence of Soul Edge, his skin gained an unnatural [[purple_skin|purple tint]] and his [[yellow_eyes|eyes turned yellow]] with the [[black_sclera|sclera turning black]]. His usually seen wearing a [[pirate_costume|pirate captain's uniform]] and wielding a [[gunblade|pistol sword]] and a large [[sword]].

title: howa_type_64
body:
Type 64 [[battle rifle]] was the predecessor of [[howa type 89|Type 89]] as the main issue rifle of the Japan Self-Defense Force (JSDF). It's designed to take a weaker load of 7.62x51 NATO (.308 Winchester) to compensate for the weaker constitution of the Japanese soldiers. Not only that but the rifles were also plagued with unreliability due to the rifle design; noted that unlike the other variants of the FN FAL, the Type 64 bolt carrier also located on top of its reciever, thus resulting in two main issues: first, the brass ejected is sent right overhead of the shooter, which may potentially injures him/her in the process and second, such design allows dust, rain and whatnot to enter the gun and causes it to malfunction. On a side note, the use of alloy and other space age materials to achieve the goal of weight reduction for the Type 64 might as well be for naught as in order to actually shoot the rifle accurately, not only the JSDF have to opt for a low-power 7.62 NATO but a permanent bipod must also be attached and this alone negates any weight advantages that the gun might have.

Nowadays it's being continually replaced with the newer Type 89.

* Caliber: 7,62x51 mm
* Action: Gas operated, tilting bolt
* Overall length: 990 mm
* Barrel length: 450 mm
* Weight: 4,3 kg less magazine
* Rate of fire: 450-500 rounds per minute
* [[magazine_(weapon)|Magazine]] capacity: 20 rounds

h4. See also

title: shinozaki_ayaka
body:
Ayaka is one of the main protagonists in [[Kami-sama no Memo-chou]]. She is [[fujishima narumi|Narumi's]] classmate and has a very active and cheerful personality. She works part-time at a [[ramen]] shop called Hanamaru. Even though she does not enjoy school that much, often skipping classes as a result, she does enjoy her school's gardening club in which she is a member.

Ayaka has a very strong relationship with [[shionji yuuko|Alice]] and is taking care of her, sometimes against Alice's will. She is the one who washes her laundry when Narumi is gone, helps her shower, takes care of her hair, helps her dress up, and teases her for her cuteness.

She is voiced by [[Kayano Ai]].

title: kami-sama_no_memo-chou
body:
lit. [i]God's Memo Pad[/i]

A 2007 light novel series by Sugii Hikaru, with illustrations by [[Kishida Mel]], adapted into a 2010 manga by [[Tiv]], serialized in ASCII Media Works' [i]Dengeki Daioh[/i], and a 2011 anime by J.C.Staff.

h4. Plot
[[Fujishima Narumi]] may seem like a normal high school student at first glance, but in reality, he is a pessimistic outsider. Due to his father's work, he had to constantly transfer schools, and thus he has never managed to become a part of society. When he is forced to join the gardening club by his cheerful classmate [[Shinozaki Ayaka]], Narumi encounters the genius hacker [[Shionji Yuuko|Alice]], who lives in isolation above Hanamaru, the ramen shop where Ayaka works part-time. He then discovers that Alice is running a special private detective agency and that all her professional associates refer to themselves as "[[neet|NEET]]"s.

Joining the NEET detective agency due to his personal connection with a criminal case, Narumi finds himself entangled in a world of dangerous investigations conducted by the ill-assorted group of detectives, all the while trying to track down the crime syndicate which seems to have mysterious ties to Alice.

title: a~_un~
body:
Most komainu statues come in pairs and are nearly identical to each other with the exception of the position of their mouth: one with their mouth open, and one with their mouth closed. 

Their mouths have significant Buddhist symbolic meaning. The open mouth is pronouncing the first letter of the Sanskrit alphabet, which is pronounced "a", while the closed one is uttering the last letter, which is pronounced "um", to represent the beginning and the end of all things. In Japanese, these two forms are called collectively a-un and individually as a-gyō (阿形) and un-gyō (吽形).

Because [[Komano Aunn]] is a komainu and her given name is Aun, fans have taken to giving her a verbal tic where she will shout her given name in two parts. It can sometimes appear as "A! NN!" or "A! UN!"

title: kariyushi_shirt
body:
Similar to a [[hawaiian shirt]], a kariyushi shirt is a collared, short-sleeved, patterned [[dress shirt]] mainly worn in summer. The shirts are made in Okinawa to promote Okinawan tourism. Kariyushi shirts often have designs based on patterns found in Okinawan art, motifs from things common to Okinawa like bitter melons or dragon boats, or [[shiisaa]]-patterned designs.

This tag will most likely be associated with [[Komano Aunn]], as her default outfit is a red komainu-patterned kariyushi shirt.
